1
00:00:39,967 --> 00:00:43,033
<i>Miss Martinez, are you sure you
want to be one</i>

2
00:00:43,167 --> 00:00:44,800
<i> of the FMP dealers?</i>

3
00:00:44,933 --> 00:00:46,633
<i>Why are you gathering
your stuff?</i>

4
00:00:46,767 --> 00:00:47,667
<i> I'm leaving.</i>

5
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:48,833
<i> Okay.</i>

6
00:00:48,967 --> 00:00:51,267
<i>That's it? So you're letting me
go just like that?</i>

7
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:53,500
<i>Paz, please. You can't change
my mind.</i>

8
00:00:53,633 --> 00:00:54,333
<i> Mom, please.</i>

9
00:00:54,467 --> 00:00:55,567
<i> Tell us the truth.</i>

10
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:58,033
<i>Please stop hiding things
from us.</i>

11
00:00:58,167 --> 00:00:59,700
<i> I'm hiding Manuel.</i>

12
00:00:59,967 --> 00:01:02,033
<i>Take me to Coleen,
I need to talk to her.</i>

13
00:01:02,167 --> 00:01:03,300
<i> But I'm still in Tarlac.</i>

14
00:01:03,433 --> 00:01:04,367
<i> I have a lot of deliveries.</i>

15
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:06,567
<i>Joel, which way are you
going again?</i>

16
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:07,867
<i>- Felma, I'm begging you.
- You're a liar!</i>

17
00:01:08,033 --> 00:01:09,833
<i> You're a lying beast!</i>

18
00:01:09,967 --> 00:01:13,200
<i>I gave you Felma's address
because you fooled me!</i>

19
00:01:13,333 --> 00:01:14,533
<i>Give me my husband back, Felma!</i>

20
00:01:14,667 --> 00:01:15,533
<i> You're a liar!</i>

21
00:01:15,667 --> 00:01:16,633
<i> You're insane!</i>

22
00:01:16,767 --> 00:01:18,200
<i>- Get out of here!
- Please...</i>

23
00:01:27,933 --> 00:01:29,267
Oh, my god!

24
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:30,467
What happened?

25
00:01:31,333 --> 00:01:33,500
Paz, that Paz dragged me out.

26
00:01:34,267 --> 00:01:34,933
What?

27
00:01:35,067 --> 00:01:36,533
You didn't fight back?

28
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:40,367
No, I just let her drag me.

29
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,733
What? Why?

30
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:44,633
To make myself
look like a victim!

31
00:01:44,767 --> 00:01:49,400
Now, everyone in there thinks
that I'm getting mistreated.

32
00:01:49,533 --> 00:01:53,400
I made it look like Felma
took my husband from me.

33
00:01:53,533 --> 00:01:56,200
All her employees couldn't
believe what they were seeing.

34
00:01:56,333 --> 00:01:58,667
That's nice,
you're so brilliant!

35
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,867
I know.

36
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:05,133
Now, I won't just ruin
that woman's reputation.

37
00:02:05,267 --> 00:02:06,800
I'll destroy the entire company.

38
00:02:07,767 --> 00:02:12,367
That woman's sausage business
will go down with her.

39
00:02:13,533 --> 00:02:14,533
Look!

40
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:16,300
Look at what they did to me!

41
00:02:16,433 --> 00:02:17,633
My god!

42
00:02:21,767 --> 00:02:23,933
I'm sorry
about the commotion earlier.

43
00:02:25,267 --> 00:02:27,500
I just want to clarify things.

44
00:02:28,767 --> 00:02:30,500
I didn't wreck anyone's home.

45
00:02:32,300 --> 00:02:33,400
But I admit...

46
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:37,400
that there's a problem.

47
00:02:38,633 --> 00:02:39,667
It's personal...

48
00:02:42,133 --> 00:02:44,167
and FMP has nothing to do
with this.

49
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:47,300
Don't ever believe
that scandalous woman.

50
00:02:47,467 --> 00:02:48,200
She's a liar!

51
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:48,967
A liar!

52
00:02:49,100 --> 00:02:49,833
Paz!

53
00:02:53,533 --> 00:02:58,067
I don't want FMP to be affected
because of my personal issues.

54
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:00,633
Whatever you heard earlier,

55
00:03:01,367 --> 00:03:04,133
I hope you won't turn it
into gossip here at work.

56
00:03:04,267 --> 00:03:08,833
If you have questions,
you'd better ask me now.

57
00:03:09,567 --> 00:03:11,233
You were right, Ma'am.

58
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:15,133
Your personal issues
do not concern the company.

59
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,500
I'll speak on behalf
of everyone.

60
00:03:19,233 --> 00:03:23,267
We won't meddle in or gossip
about your personal issues,

61
00:03:23,433 --> 00:03:25,467
especially since they have
nothing to do with FMP.

62
00:03:26,067 --> 00:03:27,600
- Right?
- Yes.

63
00:03:30,433 --> 00:03:31,867
Thank you.

64
00:03:32,933 --> 00:03:33,900
Thank you.

65
00:03:35,867 --> 00:03:36,833
Thank you.

66
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:43,267
Thank you.

67
00:03:45,733 --> 00:03:47,033
Thanks to all of you.

68
00:03:57,067 --> 00:03:59,267
Jeff, Coleen is still
not answering my calls.

69
00:03:59,933 --> 00:04:01,733
I have a feeling mom has
given her the heads up.

70
00:04:01,867 --> 00:04:03,533
<i>Andrea, don't fight with Coleen.</i>

71
00:04:03,933 --> 00:04:04,667
You'd better listen to me.

72
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,133
Don't fight with her.

73
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,600
Explain why you want
to see her dad.

74
00:04:09,733 --> 00:04:10,200
Okay?

75
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:11,467
Okay, I got it.

76
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:12,700
Students are getting out now.

77
00:04:12,833 --> 00:04:13,667
I will call you back.

78
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:14,967
I think Coleen
is on her way out.

79
00:04:15,500 --> 00:04:16,467
Okay, bye.

80
00:04:17,933 --> 00:04:19,300
Hey, Andrea.

81
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:23,233
Rona.

82
00:04:23,367 --> 00:04:24,467
Where's Coleen?

83
00:04:24,933 --> 00:04:27,233
She didn't go to school today.

84
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,800
But she called me earlier.

85
00:04:28,933 --> 00:04:33,300
She said she'll spend some time

86
00:04:33,433 --> 00:04:35,800
with some important people
in her life.

87
00:04:35,933 --> 00:04:36,833
Did she say who she's going
to be with?

88
00:04:37,567 --> 00:04:39,167
She didn't say anything.

89
00:04:39,767 --> 00:04:41,000
What about Jane?

90
00:04:41,133 --> 00:04:42,900
Do you think she knows
where Coleen is?

91
00:04:43,033 --> 00:04:44,600
Who's Jane?

92
00:04:44,733 --> 00:04:45,567
Your new classmate.

93
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:47,100
The transferee?

94
00:04:47,867 --> 00:04:52,433
We don't have a new
transferee classmate.

95
00:04:52,567 --> 00:04:53,367
What?

96
00:05:02,033 --> 00:05:03,667
<i>Why are you gathering
your stuff?</i>

97
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:04,667
<i> I'm leaving.</i>

98
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:06,067
<i> Oh, okay.</i>

99
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:06,800
<i> That's it?</i>

100
00:05:07,067 --> 00:05:08,867
<i>What else do you
want me to do?</i>

101
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:10,533
<i> You want me to stop you?</i>

102
00:05:10,667 --> 00:05:11,433
<i> Yes!</i>

103
00:05:11,567 --> 00:05:12,600
<i>Even if you don't
mean it, Felma.</i>

104
00:05:12,733 --> 00:05:14,167
<i> So that even in the end,</i>

105
00:05:14,300 --> 00:05:16,400
<i>I'll feel that
I mattered to you.</i>

106
00:05:16,533 --> 00:05:17,900
<i>That you didn't want
to let me go.</i>

107
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:20,567
<i> I owe a lot to you, but...</i>

108
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:23,167
<i>but it seems like we really
can't see eye to eye anymore.</i>

109
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:29,000
<i>Mom, what happened?
Why is Uncle Noah leaving?</i>

110
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:31,767
<i>You were right,
I'm hiding Manuel.</i>

111
00:05:32,267 --> 00:05:34,200
<i> And Noah found out.</i>

112
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:35,567
<i> What?</i>

113
00:05:37,133 --> 00:05:40,400
<i>Don't you remember
when I first came to you?</i>

114
00:05:40,933 --> 00:05:42,667
<i> I was so down.</i>

115
00:05:43,267 --> 00:05:45,267
<i> I was desperate, Paz.</i>

116
00:05:45,767 --> 00:05:46,700
<i> Do you remember?</i>

117
00:05:47,267 --> 00:05:48,767
<i> You said you would help me.</i>

118
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:50,000
<i>- Hey!
- That's why you gave me</i>

119
00:05:50,133 --> 00:05:51,133
<i> Manuel's address.</i>

120
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:53,167
<i>But Manuel was gone
when I got there.</i>

121
00:05:53,633 --> 00:05:55,733
<i> They already left.</i>

122
00:05:55,867 --> 00:05:59,467
<i>That's why you gave me
Felma's address.</i>

123
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:01,467
<i> So that I can find them.</i>

124
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,900
<i>Because you also think
that he was there!</i>

125
00:06:04,033 --> 00:06:06,000
<i> You're a lying beast!</i>

126
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:09,767
<i>You also believe that Felma
is hiding my family from me.</i>

127
00:06:09,933 --> 00:06:10,667
<i> Please.</i>

128
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:21,800
Felma.

129
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:26,867
I don't really want
to talk to you right now.

130
00:06:27,967 --> 00:06:30,033
Please don't be like this.

131
00:06:35,167 --> 00:06:36,700
You betrayed me.

132
00:06:39,233 --> 00:06:40,867
I did something wrong.

133
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,000
But I didn't betray you.

134
00:06:46,267 --> 00:06:48,767
Felma, please,
I'm begging you...

135
00:06:49,767 --> 00:06:52,233
hear me out, okay?

136
00:06:52,367 --> 00:06:53,167
Please?

137
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:04,700
Coleen, don't be sad.

138
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:06,567
Our apartment won't be far
from here,

139
00:07:06,700 --> 00:07:08,033
you can visit us anytime.

140
00:07:08,167 --> 00:07:08,967
Okay?

141
00:07:10,367 --> 00:07:12,100
That's not what
I'm sad about.

142
00:07:13,133 --> 00:07:15,500
I'm just thinking
about what you said.

143
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:19,733
You have to go
to the province to hide.

144
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:21,400
Come on.

145
00:07:21,567 --> 00:07:23,333
That's only temporary.

146
00:07:23,467 --> 00:07:27,500
We'll come back here once my mom
goes back to Canada.

147
00:07:28,533 --> 00:07:29,533
I promise.

148
00:07:30,733 --> 00:07:33,000
- Here, try this.
- Coleen.

149
00:07:36,933 --> 00:07:37,600
Andrea.

150
00:07:40,267 --> 00:07:41,567
What are you cooking?

151
00:07:44,033 --> 00:07:46,933
Is that for the
very important people

152
00:07:47,067 --> 00:07:49,800
you want to spend time with?

153
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:53,867
Where are they?

154
00:07:59,433 --> 00:08:00,767
And you?

155
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,300
Who are you really?

156
00:08:04,700 --> 00:08:07,233
Because Rona told me earlier

157
00:08:08,167 --> 00:08:15,733
that you don't have
a friend named Jane.

158
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:22,033
What, Coleen?

159
00:08:22,900 --> 00:08:23,900
Why can't you answer me?

160
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:29,300
Here, Jessica,
Mrs. Wilson is calling.

161
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:50,633
That's your dad's
daughter's name.

162
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:55,667
<i> Have some pity on my mom!</i>

163
00:08:55,933 --> 00:08:57,767
<i> Have pity on us!</i>

164
00:08:57,900 --> 00:08:59,100
<i> We're living peacefully now.</i>

165
00:08:59,233 --> 00:09:01,033
<i> Just leave us be!</i>

166
00:09:01,167 --> 00:09:02,867
<i> Please watch your words.</i>

167
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:06,300
<i>Being hurt doesn't give you
the right to disrespect others.</i>

168
00:09:06,733 --> 00:09:08,267
<i> And please, for dad's sake,</i>

169
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,567
<i>we don't need negativity
right now.</i>

170
00:09:13,467 --> 00:09:17,733
That's why you seem familiar.

171
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:22,133
That's why your voice
seems familiar.

172
00:09:24,633 --> 00:09:25,667
Now I remember.

173
00:09:29,267 --> 00:09:32,667
Because you're Jessica!

174
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:38,067
You're here, so that means
your father's here, too!

175
00:09:39,733 --> 00:09:42,000
Where are you hiding him?
In Didang's room?

176
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,333
- What?
- Andrea...

177
00:09:47,633 --> 00:09:49,867
What are you doing!
There's no such thing! Andrea!

178
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,033
- Andrea!
- Andrea!

179
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:01,033
Andrea!

180
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,267
Andrea, stop! Please!

181
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,400
- Let go of me!
- Andrea!

182
00:10:03,533 --> 00:10:04,467
- Let go of me!
- Andrea, stop!

183
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:05,200
- What's with you?
- Andrea!

184
00:10:05,367 --> 00:10:07,300
- Andrea!
- Andrea!

185
00:10:18,267 --> 00:10:18,767
- Stop!
- Andrea!

186
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:20,367
- Andrea!
- Andrea!

187
00:10:27,033 --> 00:10:28,167
Andeng?

188
00:10:28,300 --> 00:10:29,233
Dad.

189
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:44,833
<i> My contract won't take long.</i>

190
00:10:44,967 --> 00:10:45,700
<i>I'll only be gone
for two years.</i>

191
00:10:45,833 --> 00:10:46,833
<i> It will pass by quickly.</i>

192
00:10:47,367 --> 00:10:49,500
<i>Once I save up some money,
I will go home right away.</i>

193
00:10:49,633 --> 00:10:51,333
<i> We won't be separated again.</i>

194
00:10:51,900 --> 00:10:52,967
<i> I promise.</i>

195
00:10:53,900 --> 00:10:55,200
<i> Be good, okay?</i>

196
00:10:56,900 --> 00:10:58,933
<i>Always have your inhaler
with you.</i>

197
00:11:00,267 --> 00:11:02,400
<i>Whenever you get an asthma
attack, you have to rest, okay?</i>

198
00:11:03,467 --> 00:11:05,833
<i>So your heart condition
doesn't get worse, okay?</i>

199
00:11:09,567 --> 00:11:11,000
<i> How are you, Andeng?</i>

200
00:11:11,133 --> 00:11:12,167
<i> I've been a good girl.</i>

201
00:11:12,300 --> 00:11:13,933
<i>I don't run around with Mayette.</i>

202
00:11:14,067 --> 00:11:15,367
<i> Hello, Andeng, sweetie.</i>

203
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,000
<i> How are you?</i>

204
00:11:17,133 --> 00:11:23,100
<i>The doctor said
I can't laugh yet.</i>

205
00:11:23,233 --> 00:11:26,100
<i>So don't watch funny
shows yet, okay?</i>

206
00:11:27,633 --> 00:11:28,567
Andeng, sweetie.

207
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:30,333
Don't ever call me Andeng.

208
00:11:32,067 --> 00:11:33,233
What are you doing here?

209
00:11:33,733 --> 00:11:34,467
Andeng, wait.

210
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,767
Let me explain.

211
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:36,867
What is there to explain?

212
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:40,600
You're going to explain how you
abandoned us for eighteen years?

213
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:43,167
And why are you back here?

214
00:11:44,267 --> 00:11:46,267
And what are you doing here
in our house?

215
00:11:47,700 --> 00:11:49,567
Andrea, don't talk
to him like that.

216
00:11:49,700 --> 00:11:51,833
He didn't want to come here.

217
00:11:51,967 --> 00:11:53,200
But you want him to stay here!

218
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:57,033
Because you brought them here!

219
00:11:57,633 --> 00:11:59,033
You're so stubborn.

220
00:11:59,967 --> 00:12:02,133
No matter how many times
I told you...

221
00:12:03,100 --> 00:12:05,533
not to talk to this man!

222
00:12:05,667 --> 00:12:07,567
You have the nerve
to bring him here!

223
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:10,400
Andrea, I can't
just abandon them.

224
00:12:11,133 --> 00:12:12,667
If Hazel finds them,

225
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:15,500
she will bring them back
to Canada and hurt them again.

226
00:12:17,067 --> 00:12:19,533
I talked to Hazel

227
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:25,467
because I want to get Manuel
away from you.

228
00:12:26,033 --> 00:12:29,167
To get you and your children
out of trouble.

229
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:30,500
That's all I want.

230
00:12:34,533 --> 00:12:36,400
You hurt my feelings.

231
00:12:39,067 --> 00:12:41,200
We've been friends
for a long time.

232
00:12:42,033 --> 00:12:45,800
You're like a second mother
to my children.

233
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:50,800
And then, you conspired
with that woman?

234
00:12:51,633 --> 00:12:53,233
Don't you understand?

235
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:55,933
You betrayed me!

236
00:12:56,733 --> 00:13:01,200
That's why I had a feeling
that I had talked to you before.

237
00:13:01,667 --> 00:13:03,167
There's something about you.

238
00:13:03,933 --> 00:13:05,867
You lied about your name
being Jane?

239
00:13:06,533 --> 00:13:07,967
You made a fool out of me!

240
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:09,800
Andrea, I'm sorry.

241
00:13:09,933 --> 00:13:12,200
Don't ever call me that,
you're not my sister!

242
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:19,000
And you, Coleen, you didn't just
drag your father here.

243
00:13:19,133 --> 00:13:20,200
You have to bring her along,
too!

244
00:13:20,667 --> 00:13:22,067
You don't think about
how I would feel,

245
00:13:22,233 --> 00:13:22,967
how Jeffrey would feel?

246
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:25,133
Andeng, don't get mad
at your sister.

247
00:13:25,267 --> 00:13:26,667
She's just trying to help us.

248
00:13:26,900 --> 00:13:28,467
I'm not talking to you.

249
00:13:28,967 --> 00:13:31,433
Andrea, don't treat
your father like that!

250
00:13:31,567 --> 00:13:32,867
You, too!

251
00:13:34,100 --> 00:13:35,300
And you, too, Didang!

252
00:13:35,967 --> 00:13:37,333
You guys are all in this?

253
00:13:38,433 --> 00:13:41,833
No one told me that
this thing was going on?

254
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:43,967
How long have they been here?

255
00:13:46,633 --> 00:13:47,567
Since when?

256
00:13:50,067 --> 00:13:50,933
Coleen!

257
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:53,467
They've been here
since last week.

258
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:56,933
You guys are all
truly shameless!

259
00:13:57,833 --> 00:13:59,467
We were nothing but good to you!

260
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:00,733
And you, Didang!

261
00:14:01,567 --> 00:14:03,000
I was so kind to you!

262
00:14:03,767 --> 00:14:07,033
We don't deserve
to be deceived like this!

263
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:28,467
Felma, do you really think
I didn't think it through?

264
00:14:30,533 --> 00:14:33,500
Whether I should help
that beast?

265
00:14:35,100 --> 00:14:35,933
Yes...

266
00:14:36,833 --> 00:14:39,500
I knew you'd probably get mad.

267
00:14:39,633 --> 00:14:41,800
But what matters more to me

268
00:14:41,933 --> 00:14:44,400
is keeping you
and my godchildren

269
00:14:44,533 --> 00:14:45,767
away from all the trouble.

270
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:47,733
So please, Felma, please.

271
00:14:47,867 --> 00:14:51,967
I'm begging you to forgive me.

272
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:53,733
I'm sorry.

273
00:14:54,567 --> 00:14:57,433
Just try to be more
understanding.

274
00:14:57,867 --> 00:14:59,233
I'm asking you, please.

275
00:15:01,367 --> 00:15:03,733
Let's make peace.

276
00:15:07,467 --> 00:15:08,767
Hello, Coleen.

277
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:11,533
Mom, Andrea finds out the truth.

278
00:15:13,233 --> 00:15:14,067
<i> Go ahead!</i>

279
00:15:14,633 --> 00:15:16,533
Tell her!

280
00:15:16,667 --> 00:15:18,267
So we can all face
each other right here!

281
00:15:23,067 --> 00:15:25,733
- What did Coleen say?
- I need to go home.

282
00:15:25,867 --> 00:15:26,567
- What?
- I need to go home.

283
00:15:26,700 --> 00:15:29,500
Mom, where are you going?

284
00:15:29,633 --> 00:15:31,167
I need to go home.

285
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:32,267
Why?

286
00:15:37,867 --> 00:15:40,567
Coleen called her, Jeff.

287
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:42,467
What did she say again?

288
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:43,633
Bring me home.

289
00:15:43,767 --> 00:15:44,933
Mom, what's going on?

290
00:15:45,767 --> 00:15:47,400
It's just...

291
00:15:48,033 --> 00:15:50,367
Your sisters are fighting.

292
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:54,000
Andrea found out that Manuel
is staying in our house.

293
00:15:54,133 --> 00:15:55,033
What?

294
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:56,933
That's what I'm talking about.

295
00:15:57,067 --> 00:15:59,300
So that's where you're hiding
that jerk?

296
00:15:59,433 --> 00:16:00,800
Sweetie.

297
00:16:00,933 --> 00:16:03,700
- Wait, sweetie. Jeffrey!
- Jeffrey, sweetie!

298
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:04,600
Sweetie!

299
00:16:04,933 --> 00:16:07,333
So mom is in on this, too?

300
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,167
Andrea, please
don't be mad at mom.

301
00:16:10,333 --> 00:16:12,400
She wasn't in on it
with us at first.

302
00:16:12,533 --> 00:16:14,000
She only found out recently.

303
00:16:14,133 --> 00:16:15,033
Oh, really?

304
00:16:15,167 --> 00:16:16,000
And then what?

305
00:16:16,467 --> 00:16:17,900
Did she kick them out?

306
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:20,367
No, right? You all conspired
together!

307
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:23,400
The way you look at each other,
you're all lying!

308
00:16:23,533 --> 00:16:25,500
You both lied to us!

309
00:16:25,633 --> 00:16:27,367
We can't bear to not help them!

310
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:29,033
I don't care!

311
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:34,567
But I do!

312
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:37,767
Because he's still my father
and Jessica is my sister!

313
00:16:37,900 --> 00:16:38,933
And what about me?

314
00:16:39,067 --> 00:16:39,767
What about me and Jeffrey?

315
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:41,100
What are we to you?

316
00:16:41,233 --> 00:16:42,233
We're nothing to you?

317
00:16:42,967 --> 00:16:45,900
Don't be mad at Coleen, Andrea.

318
00:16:46,033 --> 00:16:48,333
I told you not to call me
your sister.

319
00:16:48,467 --> 00:16:51,367
Don't butt in because
you're not related to us!

320
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:54,100
Don't get mad at Coleen,
she's only helping us.

321
00:16:54,233 --> 00:16:56,600
We didn't plan to stay here.

322
00:16:56,733 --> 00:16:58,300
You didn't plan anything anyway.

323
00:16:59,267 --> 00:17:00,800
You didn't plan to go abroad.

324
00:17:01,267 --> 00:17:03,267
You didn't plan
to get Hazel pregnant.

325
00:17:04,533 --> 00:17:06,333
You didn't plan to abandon us!

326
00:17:07,033 --> 00:17:11,000
And now that you're disabled,
you're coming back here?

327
00:17:11,733 --> 00:17:14,000
You're going to drag us
into your mess, too!

328
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:16,167
Andrea, that's enough.

329
00:17:17,067 --> 00:17:19,467
You shouldn't disrespect
your father like that.

330
00:17:19,967 --> 00:17:21,233
If your father hadn't cared,

331
00:17:21,367 --> 00:17:22,967
you wouldn't have gotten
that operation.

332
00:17:23,100 --> 00:17:24,167
Abel.

333
00:17:24,600 --> 00:17:25,567
That's enough.

334
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:28,033
I know that.

335
00:17:29,867 --> 00:17:31,467
And I'm thankful for that.

336
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:37,033
But for you to get
another woman pregnant...

337
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:40,367
Was that part of your
sacrifice as well?

338
00:17:42,533 --> 00:17:43,533
Is that part of it?

339
00:17:49,633 --> 00:17:51,367
It's easy for you to say.

340
00:17:51,867 --> 00:17:52,667
Andeng.

341
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:54,700
Easy for you to meddle.

342
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:57,567
Because you don't know
what we've been through.

343
00:17:59,333 --> 00:18:01,100
How my mom suffered.

344
00:18:02,033 --> 00:18:03,733
How Jeffrey and I helped
each other,

345
00:18:03,867 --> 00:18:05,900
because mom couldn't do it
alone.

346
00:18:07,367 --> 00:18:08,600
Why can't she do it?

347
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:11,600
Because her husband left her!

348
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:14,367
She was all alone.

349
00:18:15,733 --> 00:18:17,500
We saw all of that.

350
00:18:17,633 --> 00:18:19,000
I saw everything!

351
00:18:26,133 --> 00:18:27,233
We crawled through life.

352
00:18:28,967 --> 00:18:31,167
We suffered, we were
so down because...

353
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:34,433
Because we don't have a father.

354
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:40,300
- Andeng, sweetie.
- Don't call me Andeng.

355
00:18:41,133 --> 00:18:42,267
And I'm not your daughter.

356
00:18:43,167 --> 00:18:45,200
My father's long been dead.

357
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:49,633
And the dead doesn't
come back to life.

358
00:18:50,967 --> 00:18:54,600
The dead brings nothing
but trouble and pain.

359
00:18:55,933 --> 00:18:57,367
And that's what you're doing.

360
00:18:58,733 --> 00:18:59,600
You're hurting us!

361
00:18:59,733 --> 00:19:00,900
You're messing with us!

362
00:19:01,433 --> 00:19:02,667
That's what you're doing!

363
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:03,600
- Move!
- Andrea!

364
00:19:03,733 --> 00:19:04,900
- I said move!
- What are you doing?

365
00:19:05,033 --> 00:19:05,700
- Andrea!
- Andrea!

366
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:07,967
- Andeng.
- Andrea, stop it!

367
00:19:08,100 --> 00:19:10,133
The way you talk to dad
is not right!

368
00:19:10,267 --> 00:19:11,733
You're going too far!

369
00:19:12,567 --> 00:19:14,800
We're not fighting
because of him!

370
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:17,100
We're fighting because
you're so unforgiving!

371
00:19:17,233 --> 00:19:19,033
You're the stubborn one!

372
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:21,867
Why are we in this situation
right now?

373
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,200
Isn't it because of him?

374
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:25,267
Why are we fighting right now?

375
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:26,667
It's because of you!

376
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:29,300
Our family's falling apart!

377
00:19:30,133 --> 00:19:32,100
Why did Mom and Uncle Noah
break up?

378
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:33,800
Isn't it because of him?

379
00:19:34,867 --> 00:19:37,033
He's my dad! He became my father
figure!

380
00:19:37,167 --> 00:19:38,467
Where is he now?

381
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:41,800
Andrea, Uncle Noah
is not our dad!

382
00:19:41,933 --> 00:19:43,200
He is our dad!

383
00:19:43,333 --> 00:19:46,833
Uncle Noah had been my father
for many years!

384
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:52,200
But because of this man,
my father is gone!

385
00:19:53,033 --> 00:19:54,267
He resigned from his job

386
00:19:54,767 --> 00:19:55,500
and went as far away
as he could from mom.

387
00:19:55,633 --> 00:19:57,167
He's not in my life anymore!

388
00:19:58,133 --> 00:20:00,567
Because of you!

389
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:04,200
You're so selfish!

390
00:20:04,333 --> 00:20:06,467
You all are selfish!

391
00:20:07,133 --> 00:20:09,100
You're the selfish one.

392
00:20:09,233 --> 00:20:11,867
Andeng, I don't plan to take
Noah's part in your life.

393
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,700
Jessica and I are leaving.

394
00:20:14,833 --> 00:20:15,933
Then go!

395
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:17,567
You guys should go!

396
00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:18,633
Get out!

397
00:20:18,767 --> 00:20:20,100
- Andeng.
- Get out!

398
00:20:20,233 --> 00:20:21,233
Andrea, stop!

399
00:20:21,367 --> 00:20:22,233
Get out!

400
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:27,967
Andrea, just let them
stay here, please.

401
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:29,067
I just talked to the landlady.

402
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:30,500
They can't move until tomorrow.

403
00:20:30,633 --> 00:20:31,733
I don't care!

404
00:20:31,867 --> 00:20:33,500
- Get out of here!
- Andrea, please!

405
00:20:33,633 --> 00:20:34,867
I'm begging you.

406
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:37,433
- Don't touch me!
- Andeng!

407
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:41,000
- Andrea, please! Stop!
- Andrea, calm down.

408
00:20:41,133 --> 00:20:42,067
Andrea!

409
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:43,867
- Get out of here!
- Andeng, I'm begging you.

410
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,300
- Get out of here!
- I'm begging you, please.

411
00:20:45,433 --> 00:20:46,133
Andeng.

412
00:20:46,267 --> 00:20:47,333
Get out!

413
00:20:47,467 --> 00:20:49,200
- Andeng, I'm begging you.
- Get out!

414
00:20:49,333 --> 00:20:51,300
- Get out!
- Please, stop!

415
00:20:51,433 --> 00:20:52,967
Please...

416
00:20:53,100 --> 00:20:54,433
I said, don't touch me!

417
00:20:54,567 --> 00:20:55,700
Andrea, stop.

418
00:20:55,833 --> 00:20:57,933
- Andrea, stop. Please, stop.
- I'm begging you, please.

419
00:20:58,067 --> 00:21:01,167
- Get out of my way!
- No!

420
00:21:01,300 --> 00:21:02,167
No!

421
00:21:02,300 --> 00:21:03,900
Calm down!

422
00:21:04,033 --> 00:21:05,167
Stop it, Andrea.

423
00:21:05,300 --> 00:21:06,633
Get out!

424
00:21:06,767 --> 00:21:08,400
Andeng, I'm begging you.

425
00:21:08,567 --> 00:21:10,033
Andeng, please.

426
00:21:10,167 --> 00:21:11,133
Let me go!

427
00:21:11,267 --> 00:21:12,633
Andeng, stop!

428
00:21:12,767 --> 00:21:14,067
Get out of here!

429
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:15,500
Andrea, stop!

430
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:27,700
Be gentle.

431
00:21:28,467 --> 00:21:29,667
That's what you get.

432
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,733
You keep attacking.

433
00:21:32,633 --> 00:21:33,733
Look at you, you got injured,

434
00:21:33,867 --> 00:21:35,567
and your clothes
are all torn up.

435
00:21:36,433 --> 00:21:38,233
You should file a case
against them.

436
00:21:39,433 --> 00:21:40,433
Report them for what?

437
00:21:41,667 --> 00:21:44,833
I didn't have proof that
they have Manuel and Jessica.

438
00:21:45,467 --> 00:21:48,000
Why don't you report what you
told the owner of this unit?

439
00:21:48,533 --> 00:21:50,133
Manuel kidnapped your daughter.

440
00:21:51,100 --> 00:21:52,733
Jessica is still a minor.

441
00:21:52,867 --> 00:21:54,233
So you have the right
to her custody

442
00:21:54,367 --> 00:21:55,867
because you're the mother.

443
00:21:58,867 --> 00:22:00,100
You have a point there.

444
00:22:01,167 --> 00:22:02,667
But it's going to be
a long process.

445
00:22:03,833 --> 00:22:04,767
But why not?

446
00:22:05,633 --> 00:22:10,067
I can file a case against Felma
for conspiring with Manuel.

447
00:22:11,167 --> 00:22:12,600
She'll be scared.

448
00:22:13,433 --> 00:22:15,967
I'm sure they'll show up.

449
00:22:21,500 --> 00:22:22,800
Jeffrey, sweetie.

450
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:25,667
Jeffrey, sweetie,
you have to calm down.

451
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,333
- I'll talk to them.
- Then what?

452
00:22:27,467 --> 00:22:28,267
Let me talk to them.

453
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,900
- I'll go inside.
- Let me pass.

454
00:22:30,033 --> 00:22:30,867
- Jeffrey!
- Auntie, please!

455
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:31,700
I don't want to hurt you!

456
00:22:31,833 --> 00:22:32,733
Jeffrey!

457
00:22:32,867 --> 00:22:34,700
Jeffrey! Hey!
Calm yourself down!

458
00:22:34,833 --> 00:22:36,000
He's still your father!

459
00:22:36,133 --> 00:22:37,733
Mom, I don't have
a father anymore!

460
00:22:38,233 --> 00:22:39,500
Can you let me go?

461
00:22:40,233 --> 00:22:42,967
Wait, you have to listen
to your mom, please.

462
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:44,000
Why should I?

463
00:22:44,667 --> 00:22:46,767
Did she listen when we told her
not to meet

464
00:22:46,900 --> 00:22:47,767
with that man anymore?

465
00:22:48,233 --> 00:22:49,733
She even brought him here!

466
00:22:49,900 --> 00:22:51,800
Didn't I already
explain what happened?

467
00:22:51,933 --> 00:22:53,367
I didn't hide them!

468
00:22:53,500 --> 00:22:57,000
And Hazel is hurting them,
that's why they're hiding.

469
00:22:57,133 --> 00:22:58,133
They're already looking
for a place

470
00:22:58,267 --> 00:22:59,367
so they can move out.

471
00:22:59,500 --> 00:23:01,533
And you believe their excuses?

472
00:23:01,667 --> 00:23:02,767
Let me talk to them!

473
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:03,667
- I will face them!
- Jeffrey!

474
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:04,533
- Don't try to stop me!
- Jeffrey!

475
00:23:04,667 --> 00:23:05,633
- Felma...
- Jeffrey, stop!

476
00:23:05,767 --> 00:23:07,567
- Don't try to stop me!
- Jeffrey!

477
00:23:07,700 --> 00:23:10,333
You're going to hurt me
for his sake?

478
00:23:10,967 --> 00:23:12,933
Andrea, please be reasonable!

479
00:23:13,067 --> 00:23:14,133
They have nowhere to go!

480
00:23:14,267 --> 00:23:15,233
Where do you want them to stay?

481
00:23:15,367 --> 00:23:16,133
On the street?

482
00:23:16,267 --> 00:23:17,000
Why not?

483
00:23:17,133 --> 00:23:18,500
That's what they deserve!

484
00:23:18,633 --> 00:23:21,600
You should go to your room then,
so you won't see them!

485
00:23:21,767 --> 00:23:24,633
They're not doing
anything to you anyway!

486
00:23:24,767 --> 00:23:25,867
- Andeng!
- You're going too far!

487
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:26,833
Andeng, enough!

488
00:23:26,967 --> 00:23:28,400
So you want me to adjust
to this situation?

489
00:23:28,533 --> 00:23:30,433
You guys are shameless!

490
00:23:30,567 --> 00:23:32,600
You're going too far!

491
00:23:32,733 --> 00:23:34,267
And who are you?

492
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:36,400
I will discipline her
because she's my sister!

493
00:23:36,533 --> 00:23:37,667
- Andeng!
- Andeng, that's enough!

494
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:40,300
We can talk about this calmly,
you know.

495
00:23:40,433 --> 00:23:42,367
I know I've done you all wrong!

496
00:23:42,500 --> 00:23:43,600
I'm glad you know!

497
00:23:43,733 --> 00:23:44,700
But please, don't hurt
each other.

498
00:23:44,833 --> 00:23:46,067
You're siblings!

499
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:47,900
Stop it, Andrea.

500
00:23:48,033 --> 00:23:48,833
Let me go!

501
00:23:48,967 --> 00:23:50,933
- Andrea, stop!
- Let me go!

502
00:23:51,067 --> 00:23:52,867
- Andrea, stop.
- Please, stop!

503
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:55,800
- I said let me go!
- What's happening here?

504
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:58,600
- Stop it.
- Let her go!

505
00:23:58,733 --> 00:23:59,833
Jeff!

506
00:24:00,467 --> 00:24:01,900
What? Are you going
to hurt Andrea?

507
00:24:02,500 --> 00:24:04,367
Jeffrey, don't talk
to him like that!

508
00:24:04,500 --> 00:24:05,833
Abel! What are you doing here?

509
00:24:05,967 --> 00:24:07,433
I knew you were hiding
something from me!

510
00:24:07,567 --> 00:24:09,700
Don't butt in!

511
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:12,267
Jeffrey, dad just tried
to defend me

512
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:14,067
because she slapped me!

513
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:16,067
Are you blaming me?

514
00:24:16,767 --> 00:24:18,067
Who's at fault here?

515
00:24:18,200 --> 00:24:19,567
Why are we fighting right now?

516
00:24:19,700 --> 00:24:20,967
Isn't it because of you and mom?

517
00:24:21,433 --> 00:24:23,267
Wait a minute.

518
00:24:23,400 --> 00:24:25,200
You have to understand
my situation.

519
00:24:25,333 --> 00:24:27,233
Your father needs help.

520
00:24:27,367 --> 00:24:28,400
You should have told us!

521
00:24:28,567 --> 00:24:30,267
How can I tell you?

522
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:33,900
When you get mad every time you
hear anything about your dad!

523
00:24:34,033 --> 00:24:35,600
You still should have told us.

524
00:24:36,033 --> 00:24:38,733
We shouldn't have secrets
in this family.

525
00:24:38,867 --> 00:24:39,500
Jeff!

526
00:24:40,033 --> 00:24:41,367
That's how our family
fell apart!

527
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,767
Didn't you hide the fact
that you weren't married?

528
00:24:45,433 --> 00:24:47,433
That's why he married
someone else!

529
00:24:47,700 --> 00:24:48,833
What happened then?

530
00:24:49,367 --> 00:24:53,233
There's only one solution
to end all this.

531
00:24:54,333 --> 00:24:55,967
Mom, make them get out of here!

532
00:24:56,267 --> 00:24:57,967
Andrea, they won't be able
to move out until tomorrow.

533
00:24:58,100 --> 00:24:59,200
This is what I'm talking about!

534
00:25:00,733 --> 00:25:01,767
Don't meddle in!

535
00:25:01,900 --> 00:25:02,767
You keep butting in

536
00:25:02,933 --> 00:25:03,700
when they're trying to kick out
our friend.

537
00:25:03,833 --> 00:25:04,967
Paz!

538
00:25:05,500 --> 00:25:06,833
I don't know about you, Jeffrey.

539
00:25:07,133 --> 00:25:10,533
But I can't live in this house
with that man!

540
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:13,933
Jeff!

541
00:25:14,067 --> 00:25:14,900
Jeff!

542
00:25:15,033 --> 00:25:16,300
- What are you doing?
- Let me be!

543
00:25:19,533 --> 00:25:20,833
I said let me be!

544
00:25:31,133 --> 00:25:32,067
Andeng, stop it!

545
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:35,100
Stop that!

546
00:25:43,133 --> 00:25:44,133
To put an end to this...

547
00:25:44,467 --> 00:25:47,800
Fine, they can stay here
until tomorrow.

548
00:25:47,933 --> 00:25:51,300
But if they don't leave by then,
I will.

549
00:25:51,433 --> 00:25:55,233
We'll be able to pay tomorrow,
and we'll move out right away.

550
00:25:55,367 --> 00:25:56,900
Will I still see you again?

551
00:25:57,033 --> 00:25:58,700
You and Jessica
should stay here.

552
00:25:58,833 --> 00:26:00,867
So we can all be together.

553
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:02,733
Coleen, that's not possible.

554
00:26:02,867 --> 00:26:05,033
Why not?

555
00:26:05,167 --> 00:26:09,167
If Andrea can make a decision,
then I can too.

556
00:26:09,333 --> 00:26:13,200
I want dad and Jessica
to stay here.

557
00:26:13,467 --> 00:26:15,700
If you kick them out,
I will go with them.

558
00:26:15,833 --> 00:26:17,200
No one's leaving this house!

559
00:26:17,333 --> 00:26:20,433
Even Manuel and Jessica
are not leaving!

560
00:26:20,567 --> 00:26:21,333
I'm an adult now, Mom!

561
00:26:21,467 --> 00:26:23,000
I can take care of myself.

562
00:26:23,133 --> 00:26:26,133
So if you want to take care
of your crippled ex,

563
00:26:26,267 --> 00:26:28,467
then go ahead! Be together!

564
00:26:28,600 --> 00:26:29,167
Mom!
